eople.", "last_comment_created": 1770995622020, "content": "", "score_down": 2, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 104, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2022080639630213133", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASFhUnnmL", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 1138, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8416831, "raw_content": "", "author": "PiratePatriotParrot", "created": 1770938588463, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "IForgotToAddAnEmail", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASFhUnnmL.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/Rightanglenews/status/2022080639630213133?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Drug tents are now popping up across Zohran Mamdani\u2019s NYC, with drugs being sold openly, prices boldly displayed, and police doing nothing.", "last_comment_created": 1771014164495, "content": "", "score_down": 2, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 119, "score_up": 1140, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 61, "created": 1770936567000, "id": "2022080639630213133", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2022080565600571392/img/ykr1tbar_xBfiVyF.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2022080565600571392/pl/eFPbwMCP5enbgfCD.m3u8?v=cfc", "aspectRatio": [701, 539], "heightRatio": 76, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2022080565600571392/vid/avc1/350x270/o4UoR5Mpf4Z2YNrT.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1708618407959023617/xedffm3W_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Right Angle News Network", "username": "Rightanglenews"}, "content": "BREAKING - Drug tents are now popping up across Zohran Mamdani\u2019s NYC, with drugs being sold openly, prices boldly displayed, and police doing nothing.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 449}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASFhVwT9K", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 103, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8417906, "raw_content": "If you're wondering why Trump is finding it so difficult to dismanltle the Deep State and cast the legacy 'government' into the fire, then consider the innate fail-safe built into the presidential system. \n\nEven if a person of decent morals ever should enter the position, they will, by design, be dragged under by the psychological horror of being the locus of global attention.\n\nThe founding-fathers were concerned that a presidential system might turn into a rolling-monarchy; and for a long-while it has been. Trump was supposed to change this. However, he faces a MASSIVE psychological challenge.\n\nIn Neuropolitique (1988),  Dr Timothy Leary described it in this way: \n\n>Power corrupts, rots, destroys, curses those who impose their rules upon others. We can only explain the addictive inability of politicians to recognize this historical fact as another one of those weird and faulty wirings that incapacitate the crippled nervous systems of our species.\n\n>Enormous psychic energies are directed towards the person\nwho assumes the position of global power-holder. Unless\nthis person possesses extraordinary psychological strength,\nclarity, and flexibility, his neurology blows a fuse.\n\nWill Trump throw the ring into the fire? This will be determined by the measure of his courage, and capacity to defend the rights of children above the evil of demons.\n\nIn short: Trump must remember how it was to be a child, and act from the core of his soul. Few adults can do this, let alone the most powerful adult in the world.\n\nSource: \u201cNeuropolitique\u201d, New Falcon Press - Second Printing (1991): 47. International Standard Book Number: 1-56184-012-2, Library of Congress Card Catalog Number: 88-81431", "author": "infinite-lives", "created": 1770985477273, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "GentleSlayer", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Being 'President' is like carrying the 'Ring' in Lord of the Rings: Anyone who carries it for too long is at risk of turning into Gollum. Trump faces his most challenging test yet: Can he throw the 'ring' into the fire and dismantle the pedophile-empire, as promised? Or will the seduction take hold?", "last_comment_created": 1771006934603, "content": "<p>If you're wondering why Trump is finding it so difficult to dismanltle the Deep State and cast the legacy 'government' into the fire, then consider the innate fail-safe built into the presidential system.</p>\n<p>Even if a person of decent morals ever should enter the position, they will, by design, be dragged under by the psychological horror of being the locus of global attention.</p>\n<p>The founding-fathers were concerned that a presidential system might turn into a rolling-monarchy; and for a long-while it has been. Trump was supposed to change this. However, he faces a MASSIVE psychological challenge.</p>\n<p>In Neuropolitique (1988),  Dr Timothy Leary described it in this way:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Power corrupts, rots, destroys, curses those who impose their rules upon others. We can only explain the addictive inability of politicians to recognize this historical fact as another one of those weird and faulty wirings that incapacitate the crippled nervous systems of our species.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Enormous psychic energies are directed towards the person\nwho assumes the position of global power-holder. Unless\nthis person possesses extraordinary psychological strength,\nclarity, and flexibility, his neurology blows a fuse.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Will Trump throw the ring into the fire? This will be determined by the measure of his courage, and capacity to defend the rights of children above the evil of demons.</p>\n<p>In short: Trump must remember how it was to be a child, and act from the core of his soul. Few adults can do this, let alone the most powerful adult in the world.</p>\n<p>Source: \u201cNeuropolitique\u201d, New Falcon Press - Second Printing (1991): 47. International Standard Book Number: 1-56184-012-2, Library of Congress Card Catalog Number: 88-81431</p>\n", "score_down": 3, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 25, "score_up": 106, "is_edited": true, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASFhX2foO", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 60, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8418188, "raw_content": "", "author": "thegatewaybandit", "created": 1770996004505, "profile_picture": "1qpJFj98jqcr", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Rudy_DankMemer"